  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Better service provision to member cooperatives</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Background proposed actions and choices madeNDFU was established in 2010 and became legally registered on 11 July 2011. It is made by 15 primary cooperatives all of whom are involved in dairy farming and Milk Business in Nyagatare district. Its main business activity is marketing the aggregated milk from 15 dairy member cooperatives and supply between 50 000 to 60 000 liters of milk to Inyange Savannah Milk Factory (branch of Inyange Industries  the leading Milk Processor in Rwanda) ldquo;. During the assessment  NDFU was advised to create a SMART Strategic Plan by clearly stating a common vision and mission  the strategic goals for the coming 5 years as well as a roadmap on how to achieve the goals. Also  different aspects to improve the organization functioning  management and leadership were also discussed as main activities to start with in the collaboration with Agriterra. The Eastern part of Rwanda experiences dryness and shortage of water and animal feeds affects not only animals but the overall agriculture in the area except irrigated lands. To resolve those challenges  the union is exploring two new businesses which are investing in a water tank Truck for Farm Water Supply and to become a dealer on behalf of its members and ensure inputs supply to MCCs Animal Drugs Pharmacy. .</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Official Launch collaboration Agriterra and NDFU: an event to explain the partnershipLivestock FFS: farmer field school on good dairy farming practicesExternal audit 2017 and 2018: building on the experience with another farmer cooperative union  we will support member cooperatives in getting their audit  as well as the union.Strategic planning workshop: creation of a strategic plan for the union.Training My Coop: a training on modules 1 and 2 will be organized to strengthen the understanding of the cooperative principlesKick off workshop Youth participation in cooperatives: to engage youth in dairy farming and the cooperative.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To strengthen the positioning of the union as a service provider to their member cooperatives.</narrative>
  </description>
